1.title: Wendy Williams and Kim Kardashian
1.plot: Fantasia goes undercover auditioning for a musical based on her life. Do her fans think her success comes from her talent or sympathetic story? Rapper Lil' Kim goes undercover at a VIP listening party, trying to find out if her fans are still hardcore.

2.title: Coco
2.plot: Ice-T goes undercover in a focus group to evaluate a series of "Ice-T" products. Will fans call him a sell out? Coco goes undercover at a casting call to find a body double for her show. Will the models see Coco as a trophy wife or a true talent?

3.title: LuAnn De Lesseps and Kandi Burrus
3.plot: LuAnn de Lesseps (Bravo's The Real Housewives of New York City) goes undercover at a fake luncheon for wealthy fans to find out if money will buy you class. Meanwhile, Kandi Burruss (Bravo's "The Real Housewives of Atlanta") goes undercover at a trunk show to find out if fans still see her as a role model despite her risqué business.

4.title: Joey Fatone and Jaleel White
4.plot: Singer and television personality Joey Fatone goes undercover as a trainee on a 90s boy band tour bus. How will fans rank him amongst the other *NSYNC members? Actor Jaleel White goes undercover at a celebrity auction for Steve Urkel memorabilia. Will bidders feel he's shed his nerdy image?

5.title: Anthony Anderson and T-Pain
5.plot: Rapper T-Pain goes undercover creating memorabilia for celebrities. Do his coworkers think T-Pain is an auto-tuned phony? Actor and comedian Anthony Anderson goes undercover as a chef testing out high-end meals in a Compton restaurant. Has Anthony lost touch with his roots?

6.title: Chilli and Adrienne Bailon
6.plot: Singer and actress Adrienne Bailon goes undercover auditioning men to be Adrienne's new boyfriend. Do men love her, or are they looking for fame? Singer Chilli goes undercover casting back up dancers for TLC's new music project. Do fans really want a TLC comeback?

7.title: Fantasia Barrino and Lil Kim
7.plot: Fantasia goes undercover auditioning for a musical based on her life. Do her fans think her success comes from her talent or sympathetic story? Rapper Lil' Kim goes undercover at a VIP listening party, trying to find out if her fans are still hardcore.

imdb.plot outline: Oxygen Media disguises famous faces in pop culture on the hilarious new hidden camera series "Celebrities Undercover." From Executive Producer Wendy Williams, the half-hour series will feature two celebrities concealing their true identity with the use of prosthetic make-up to find out what unsuspecting fans and friends really think of them without the distraction of their famous personas. From TV to music, "Celebrities Undercover" will feature a wide range of celebrities like they've never been seen before including T-Pain, Fantasia, Joey Fatone, Lil' Kim, Chili, Anthony Anderson, Jaleel White, Adrienne Bailon, Ice-T and Coco and "Real Housewives" franchise stars Luann De Lesseps and Kandi Burruss.
